SB 876/25 – FIN CF SB 496
By: Delegates Martinez, Miller, Alston, Guzzone, Hill, Kaufman, Rosenberg, Ross,
Taveras, and White Holland White Holland, Bagnall, Cullison, S. Johnson,
and Lopez
Introduced and read first time: February 4, 2026
Assigned to: Health
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: February 18, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Medical Assistance Program – Coverage for the Treatment of Obesity
3 – Authorization
4 FOR the purpose of authorizing, beginning on a certain date, the Maryland Medical
5 Assistance Program to provide comprehensive coverage for the treatment of obesity;
6 requiring the Maryland Department of Health to provide notice to Program
7 recipients if the Department elects to provide the coverage; requiring, on or before a
8 certain date, the Maryland Department of Health to apply to the Centers for
9 Medicare and Medicaid Services for a State plan amendment authorizing the State
10 to provide comprehensive coverage for the treatment of obesity; and generally
11 relating to the Maryland Medical Assistance Program and coverage for the treatment
12 of obesity.
13 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
14 Article – Health – General
15 Section 15–103(a)(1)
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
19 Article – Health – General
20 Section 15–103(a)(2)(xxvii) and (xxviii)
21 Annotated Code of Maryland
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0813*

2 HOUSE BILL 813
1 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
2 BY adding to
3 Article – Health – General
4 Section 15–103(a)(2)(xxix) and 15–160
5 Annotated Code of Maryland
6 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
7 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
8 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
9 Article – Health – General
10 15–103.
11 (a) (1) The Secretary shall administer the Maryland Medical Assistance
12 Program.
13 (2) The Program:
14 (xxvii) Beginning on January 1, 2026, if providing coverage for
15 the delivery of anesthesia, shall provide coverage for the delivery of anesthesia in
16 accordance with § 15–862 of the Insurance Article; [and]
17 (xxviii) Beginning on January 1, 2026, shall provide calcium score
18 testing in accordance with § 15–863 of the Insurance Article; AND
19 (XXIX) BEGINNING ON JANUARY 1, 2027, MAY PROVIDE
20 COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE FOR THE TREATMENT OF OBESITY UNDER § 15–160 OF
21 THIS SUBTITLE.
22 15–160.
23 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE FOR THE TREATMENT
24 OF OBESITY” INCLUDES COVERAGE FOR INTENSIVE BEHAVIORAL THERAPY,
25 BARIATRIC SURGERY, AND ANY MEDICATION APPROVED BY THE FEDERAL FOOD
26 AND DRUG ADMINISTRATION WITH AN INDICATION FOR CHRONIC WEIGHT
27 MANAGEMENT IN PATIENTS WITH OBESITY.
28 (B) THE PROGRAM MAY PROVIDE COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE FOR THE
29 TREATMENT OF OBESITY.
30 (C) THE PROGRAM MAY UNDERTAKE UTILIZATION MANAGEMENT TO
31 DETERMINE THE MEDICAL NECESSITY AND APPROPRIATENESS FOR TREATMENT OF
32 OBESITY UNDER THIS SECTION IF THE DETERMINATIONS ARE MADE IN THE SAME

HOUSE BILL 813 3
1 MANNER AS DETERMINATIONS ARE MADE FOR THE TREATMENT OF ANY OTHER
2 ILLNESS, CONDITION, OR DISORDER COVERED BY THE PROGRAM.
3 (D) IF THE DEPARTMENT ELECTS TO PROVIDE COMPREHENSIVE COVERAGE
4 FOR THE TREATMENT OF OBESITY UNDER THIS SECTION, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL
5 PROVIDE NOTICE TO PROGRAM RECIPIENTS.
6 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, on or before January 1, 2027,
7 the Maryland Department of Health shall apply to the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid
8 Services for a State plan amendment that authorizes the State to provide comprehensive
9 coverage for the treatment of obesity.
10 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, on or before November 1,
11 2027, the Maryland Department of Health shall report to the Senate Finance Committee,
12 the Senate Budget and Taxation Committee, the House Health Committee, and the House
13 Appropriations Committee, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article,
14 on whether the Maryland Medical Assistance Program has begun to provide comprehensive
15 coverage for the treatment of obesity as authorized under § 15–160 of the Health – General
16 Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act, and if not, why the Department has not begun
17 to provide coverage.
18 SECTION 3. 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
19 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
